interface OrderFilters { userId?: number; status?: string }
interface OrderListResult {
  orders: Order[];
  summary: { count: number; totalRevenue: number };
}
function listOrders(filters: OrderFilters): OrderListResult
```
Logic to move from `GET /orders`:
- Filter by `userId` and/or `status`
- Compute `totalRevenue` (sum of `order.total`, rounded)
- Return `{ orders: filtered, summary: { count, totalRevenue } }`

---

**`getOrderById(id)`** — can 404
```ts
type EnrichedOrderItem = OrderItem & { productName: string }
type EnrichedOrder = Omit<Order, 'items'> & { items: EnrichedOrderItem[] }
function getOrderById(id: number): ServiceResult<EnrichedOrder>
```
Logic to move from `GET /orders/:id`:
- `orders.find(o => o.id === id)` → 404 if missing
- `enrichedItems = order.items.map(item => ({ ...item, productName: products.find(p => p.id === item.productId)?.name ?? "Unknown" }))`
- Return `{ ok: true, data: { ...order, items: enrichedItems } }`

---

**`createOrder(input)`** — can 400
```ts
function createOrder(input: CreateOrderInput): ServiceResult<Order>
```
Logic to move from `POST /orders`:
- Validate `input.userId` and `input.items` present and array → 400 `"userId and items are required"`
- Validate `input.items.length > 0` → 400 `"Order must have at least one item"`
- For each item:
  - Find product → 400 `"Product {id} not found"` if missing
  - Validate `quantity > 0` → 400 `"Quantity must be positive"`
  - Validate `product.stock >= quantity` → 400 `"Insufficient stock for {name}"`
  - Deduct stock: `product.stock -= item.quantity`
  - Accumulate `orderItems` and `total`
- Build order object with `getNextOrderId()`, status `"pending"`, `createdAt: new Date().toISOString()`
- Push to `orders` array; return `{ ok: true, data: order }`

---

**`updateOrderStatus(id, status)`** — can 400/404
```ts
function updateOrderStatus(id: number, status: string): ServiceResult<Order>
```
Logic to move from `PATCH /orders/:id/status`:
- Find order → 404 if missing
- Validate `status` is in `["pending","confirmed","shipped","delivered"]` → 400 `"Invalid status..."`
- Validate transition via `transitions` map → 400 `"Cannot transition from X to Y"`
- Mutate `order.status`; return `{ ok: true, data: order }`

> Note: the status string presence check is HTTP input — keep in route handler.

---

## Step 3 — Refactor `src/routes/products.ts`

Import the three service functions. Each handler becomes:

```ts
// GET /products
router.get("/products", (req, res) => {
  const { category, minPrice, maxPrice } = req.query;
  res.json(listProducts({
    category: typeof category === "string" ? category : undefined,
    minPrice: typeof minPrice === "string" && !isNaN(parseFloat(minPrice)) ? parseFloat(minPrice) : undefined,
    maxPrice: typeof maxPrice === "string" && !isNaN(parseFloat(maxPrice)) ? parseFloat(maxPrice) : undefined,
  }));
});

// GET /products/:id
router.get("/products/:id", (req, res) => {
  const result = getProductById(parseInt(req.params.id, 10));
  if (!result.ok) { res.status(result.status).json({ error: result.error }); return; }
  res.json(result.data);
});

// PATCH /products/:id/stock
router.patch("/products/:id/stock", (req, res) => {
  const { adjustment } = req.body as { adjustment: number };
  if (typeof adjustment !== "number") { res.status(400).json({ error: "adjustment must be a number" }); return; }
  const result = adjustProductStock(parseInt(req.params.id, 10), adjustment);
  if (!result.ok) { res.status(result.status).json({ error: result.error }); return; }
  res.json(result.data);
});
```

